<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1689,2038]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1689,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Male</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[274,497,1689,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">female and nymph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[512,579,1689,1714]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Color</emphasis>
. Crown with faint light brown markings. Tegmina with numerous veins and some cells dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[424,550,1725,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1287,1309]" captionTargetBox="[155,1414,215,1215]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[155,1440,215,1258]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5a–l. Discolopeus gen.n. species; habitus. D. diacaenus sp.n.; a. Biesiesfontein, male, yellow form; b. Calvinia, male; c. Biesiesfontein, male; d, e. Rondekop, male and female respectively; f. Doring River, male; g. Wiedouw, female; D. lissus sp.n.; h, i. Garies, male and female respectively; D. colopeus sp.n., Biesiesfontein; j, k, l. Female, male, pale form, male, dark form respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626821/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
Figs 5h, 
<date box="[525,550,1725,1750]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">5i</date>
</figureCitation>
). Nymph, based on two specimens, early and late instar respectively, with the former ochraceous, and the latter with median light brown band on ochraceous ground colour.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1689,2038]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1797,1822]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,450,1797,1822]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Measurements</emphasis>
. Overall length 
<quantity box="[636,804,1797,1822]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7199999999999998" metricValueMax="3.91" metricValueMin="3.53" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="3.7199999999999998" valueMax="3.91" valueMin="3.53">3.53–3.91 mm</quantity>
; crown length 
<quantity box="[973,1141,1797,1822]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="4.9" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="0.51" valueMax="0.53" valueMin="0.49">0.49–0.53 mm</quantity>
; crown length next to eye 
<quantity box="[151,322,1833,1857]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="0.41" valueMax="0.42" valueMin="0.4">0.40–0.42 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity box="[543,715,1833,1857]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="0.41" valueMax="0.43" valueMin="0.39">0.39–0.43 mm</quantity>
; head width 1.0 9– 
<quantity box="[937,1045,1833,1857]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.19" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="1.19">1.19 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
<quantity box="[1260,1432,1833,1857]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.075" metricValueMax="1.13" metricValueMin="1.02" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="1.075" valueMax="1.13" valueMin="1.02">1.02–1.13 mm</quantity>
; ocellus diameter 28.0 µm; interocellar distance 40.0–43.2 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1689,2038]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,151,861]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1905,1930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[279,389,1905,1930]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Genital capsule dorsally in 
<figureCitation box="[736,822,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
, laterally in 
<figureCitation box="[977,1065,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
. Tergite X anteroventrally with membranous concavity (
<figureCitation box="[429,513,1941,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with medial margins divergent, lateroposterior margin angulate (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Ratio of length of subgenital plate medially/greatest width = 1.3 7–1.72 (n=10). Aedeagus with shaft without paired tooth, but sclerotized anterior, apical lip (
<figureCitation box="[807,926,2013,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 3d, e</figureCitation>
), shaft curved dorsad at base (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1375,2013,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 3b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1391,1422,2013,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1389,1411]" captionTargetBox="[162,1447,193,1338]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1447,193,1365]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2a–g. Discolopeus diacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp.; male and female genitalia; line drawing. Posterior abdominal apodeme; a. Anterior view; b. Dorsal view; Sternite VII, specimen localities; c. Biesiesfontein; d. Wiedouw; e. Bitterfontein; f. Rondekop; g. Nuwerus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626815/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">2d</figureCitation>
); dorsal apodeme inverted V-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[575,661,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
), distal half sclerotized, proximal half compressed, unsclerotized; preatrium depressed, weakly connected to aedeagus ventrally at base of inverted V-shaped dorsal apodeme; paraphysis long, thin tubular (
<figureCitation box="[483,599,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
Figs 
<date box="[539,563,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">3i</date>
, 3j
</figureCitation>
), apex with ventral margin serrate and fine striate sculpture (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1359,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Figs 3h</figureCitation>
). Style with apophysis digitate in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[596,676,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
), compressed in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1098,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1530,1552]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1482]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,1509]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3a–p. Discolopeus lissus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f, g. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; h. Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; i, j. Aedeagal process, laterally and dorsally respectively; k, l, m. Valvifers 1, variation in shape, viewed laterally; n, o. Sternite VII, variation in posterior margin; p. Connective, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626817/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1068,1098,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Connective transverse, stem short, bar-like, arms almost right-angled (
