<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,799,824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Remarks</emphasis>
. The recognition of this species is based on male genitalia. The colour pattern of the crown resembles that of some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[569,717,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis box="[569,717,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[771,905,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colopeus">
<emphasis box="[771,905,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">D. colopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Distribution map is in 
<figureCitation box="[1171,1266,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1466]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1474]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19a–c. Distribution maps of leafhopper species of Discolopeus gen.n. and associated plants. a. Hyaenanche globosa near Vanrhynsdorp and one record near Citrusdal (red squares); b. Potential natural distribution of D. copeus sp.n. in the southwestern parts of South Africa, Western Cape Province; c. Point distributions of D. colopeus sp.n., D. lissus sp.n., D. tetracaenus sp.n., D. thigmacaenus sp.n., D. triacaenus sp.n. and D. viraktamathi sp.n. in Western, Northern and Eastern Cape Provinces." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626849/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 19c</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
